Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.06,0:00:08.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fairy Tail has been completely absorbed \Nby the hyperspace magic Anima,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.84,0:00:12.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,which was used by an alternate world Edolas
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.74,0:00:15.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,that has begun to lose its magic power.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.63,0:00:22.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu, Happy, Wendy, and Carla have headed \Nto Edolas to rescue their friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.60,0:00:26.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,where they meet the members \Nof the Edolas Fairy Tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.27,0:00:32.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, Edolas's Erza is a \Ncaptain in the Royal Army,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.51,0:00:36.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but is also known by the \Ntitle "Fairy Hunter Erza".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.91,0:02:14.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Edolas's Fairy Tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.96,0:02:17.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.20,0:02:20.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You came from another world \Ncalled Earthland, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.04,0:02:23.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And you came to Edolas in \Norder to rescue your friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.45,0:02:23.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.50,0:02:27.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And there's a Fairy Tail in that world, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.62,0:02:29.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And Erza is on your side over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.17,0:02:31.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.69,0:02:32.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.70,0:02:35.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not so easy to swallow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.70,0:02:41.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's true that this Natsu \Nisn't the Natsu we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.53,0:02:43.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing they have in \Ncommon is the way they look.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.55,0:02:44.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can say that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.69,0:02:51.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Key of Hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.11,0:02:57.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This girl is who I am in that other world?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.92,0:02:58.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.27,0:03:00.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're all tiny, Wendy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.43,0:03:04.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, we'd like you to tell \Nus how to get to the Royal City.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.68,0:03:11.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Our friends have been sucked \Nup by this world's king!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.97,0:03:14.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't rescue them soon, everyone \Nwill be converted into magic power...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.93,0:03:17.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll be gone forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.21,0:03:21.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to tell you, li'l me, but \Nyou'd be better off stopping now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.25,0:03:25.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go against Edolas's king, \Nand you forfeit your lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.66,0:03:30.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just how powerful the kingdom is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.93,0:03:35.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic power is limited in this \Nworld. It's not infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.04,0:03:38.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To put it another way, it'll \Nbe used up eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.64,0:03:42.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fearing that, the King of Edolas \Ntried to monopolize all magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.11,0:03:44.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Juvia-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.09,0:03:50.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to that, all Wizard Guilds \Nwere ordered to disband.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.05,0:03:54.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone resisted at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.45,0:03:58.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But one after another were crushed before \Nthe might of the Royal Army's magic regiments.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.39,0:04:01.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only guild that is left.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.39,0:04:03.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And of course, we haven't \Nbeen spared casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.56,0:04:06.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We've lost almost half our members.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.91,0:04:08.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The master, as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.00,0:04:09.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it all...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.02,0:04:15.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It takes all we got just to \Nkeep one step ahead of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.57,0:04:17.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So you should stay away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.75,0:04:19.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go back to your world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.17,0:04:23.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please. Tell us the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.00,0:04:28.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I will save my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.07,0:04:28.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.05,0:04:48.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Royal City of Edolas.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.83,0:04:51.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The United Chiefs of Staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.15,0:04:55.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.17,0:04:55.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.91,0:04:58.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Check out that giant lacrima!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.54,0:05:00.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw when it got here, Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.73,0:05:01.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite pretty, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.20,0:05:05.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's like tens of thousands \Nof Earthland people's magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.15,0:05:09.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,More precisely, one should say, it's \Nthe magical power of about 100 wizards,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.38,0:05:13.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,plus a great deal of other living things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.75,0:05:17.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't sweat the details, Sugar Boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.66,0:05:20.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What I was tryin' to say, \Nwas how it was like, whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.74,0:05:26.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This man is Captain of the Third Magic \NRegiment of the Royal Army, Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.10,0:05:32.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And similarly, he is Captain of the Fourth \NMagic Regiment of the Royal Army, Sugar Boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.32,0:05:38.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, the Captain of the Second Magic \NRegiment of the Royal Army, Erza Knightwalker.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.38,0:05:42.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Also known as Fairy Hunter Erza.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.63,0:05:45.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, dudes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.40,0:05:48.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When I say "whoa", it ain't like, kinda whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.19,0:05:49.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like, whoa whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.78,0:05:52.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.50,0:05:56.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Mizz Erza, have you not \Nyet done in Fairy Tail?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.99,0:05:57.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Byro!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.60,0:06:02.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're starting to give the designation \N"Fairy Hunter" a bad name...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.04,0:06:06.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This man is the Chief of Staff \Nof the Royal Army, Byro.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.49,0:06:11.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The only guild left iz now Fairy Tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.13,0:06:15.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they are the guild \Nthat runz the fastest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.55,0:06:18.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But our highnezz will be \Nexpecting results soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.78,0:06:24.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be hasty. The day our goddess \Ncatches her Fairy prey will come soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.13,0:06:26.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.27,0:06:29.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza's sword is like, whoa, man! Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.95,0:06:34.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop laughing in that freaky manner, Byro.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.92,0:06:36.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Panther Lily.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.65,0:06:39.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not like those with loud mouths.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.53,0:06:42.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That includes you, Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.96,0:06:48.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This man is Captain of the First Magic \NRegiment of the Royal Army, Panther Lily.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.04,0:06:50.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What, me too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.55,0:06:54.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you think this is more \Nlike, whoa, than any of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.97,0:06:56.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut your mouth for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.10,0:06:59.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Not in a good mood, Lily?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.83,0:07:07.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't seem pleased with \Nthe recent military buildup.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.82,0:07:10.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He should have welcomed \Nit as a military man...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.88,0:07:14.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,However, our kingdom basically \Nencompasses the entire world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.64,0:07:18.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is true that there is no obvious reason \Nfor a further strengthening of the army.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.70,0:07:23.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it because there are still \Na few pockets of resistance?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.50,0:07:25.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If that were it, we alone \Nwould easily suffice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.71,0:07:27.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.88,0:07:30.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa man, this is all so like, complicated...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.08,0:07:31.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.47,0:07:38.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.14,0:07:40.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.49,0:07:44.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.55,0:07:48.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We will be able to extract magic power
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.38,0:07:51.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,from the giant lacrima after \N4 days, right on schedule!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.38,0:07:56.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This girl is the Aide to the Chief \Nof Staff of the Royal Army, Coco.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.55,0:07:57.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.30,0:08:00.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Not enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.75,0:08:08.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your highness, what did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.13,0:08:11.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I said it was not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.82,0:08:13.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If I may, your highness...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.25,0:08:17.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That lacrima represents the magic \Npower of an entire Earthland city!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.38,0:08:21.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's enough to power the kingdom's \Nmagic for the next 10 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.87,0:08:27.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Our great kingdom of Edolas \Nmust have no limits.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.46,0:08:30.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Give it to us...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.88,0:08:32.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Give more magic power to us...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.34,0:08:36.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What I seek is eternity!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.00,0:08:38.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,An endless supply of magic power!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.78,0:08:43.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And this man is the king of Edolas, Faust!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.35,0:08:51.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay... Stay right there...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.00,0:08:56.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.28,0:08:59.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is he doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.33,0:09:02.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how much longer 'til \Nwe get to the Royal City...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.20,0:09:04.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We just left, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.39,0:09:06.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And they told us it would \Ntake 5 days to walk there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.94,0:09:11.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Our Aera aren't working properly, \Nso we have no choice but to walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.24,0:09:15.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we really not use magic anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.04,0:09:16.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.00,0:09:19.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it doesn't bode well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.99,0:09:27.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy, help out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.99,0:09:29.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen a frog like this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.10,0:09:31.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bring it back as a present for Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.95,0:09:34.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think she'll like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.45,0:09:40.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.98,0:09:45.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu, it's attacking!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.29,0:09:46.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.47,0:09:47.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fist of the...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.70,0:09:55.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot I can't use magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.69,0:10:02.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup! I can't use magic, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.15,0:10:07.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I'll do it even without magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.84,0:10:12.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.20,0:10:28.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Scary Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.75,0:10:30.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Scary Lucy-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.07,0:10:32.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit calling me "scary"!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.57,0:10:38.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy wasn't much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.38,0:10:39.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.20,0:10:46.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's... not like I was worried \Nabout you, or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.77,0:10:50.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You say a lot of stuff, but \Nyou're Lucy, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.58,0:10:52.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How does that follow exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.16,0:10:53.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See, those kinds of lines are totally "Lucy".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.08,0:10:57.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna show Lucy this scary Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.06,0:10:59.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait to see the look \Non the real one's face!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.33,0:11:01.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm a fake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.92,0:11:04.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Technique 12: The Back-Crack Bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.59,0:11:07.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup, she's scary all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.77,0:11:09.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can this continue for 5 days?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.14,0:11:12.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell it's going to \Nbe hard going... Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.68,0:11:17.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.02,0:11:20.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been thrown to one whacked out place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.95,0:11:23.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh... This is messed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.94,0:11:36.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. They thought you were \NExceeds, and reported it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.00,0:11:37.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what drew them to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.63,0:11:40.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I still can't believe that Erza's our enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.65,0:11:43.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, either one's scary, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.80,0:11:44.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.53,0:11:46.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no... I was talking about Erza!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.75,0:11:51.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To us, what's unbelievable is that \Nwe could ever get along with Erza.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.07,0:11:53.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Mysterious, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.71,0:11:55.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't a wizard out \Nthere who doesn't fear her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.43,0:11:58.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just seeing her face means certain death.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.54,0:12:00.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}really{\i0} don't want to run into her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.45,0:12:02.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The one I know is scary enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.35,0:12:05.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, we're here. Can you see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.96,0:12:08.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a city, Happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.12,0:12:10.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Walking for days sure was tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.33,0:12:12.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The buildings are kind of round?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.45,0:12:14.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.20,0:12:17.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much for coming with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.59,0:12:19.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,F-Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.13,0:12:23.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't be able to go any farther \Nwithout some magic weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.35,0:12:26.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks a bunch, Scary Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.20,0:12:27.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Scary Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.25,0:12:28.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You pickin' a fight?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.03,0:12:32.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the city of Louen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.00,0:12:37.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Until a little while ago, magic \Nwas bought and sold normally.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.95,0:12:42.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, with the kingdom's Guild Hunt, \Ntrafficking in magic is forbidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.46,0:12:46.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's not all. Even \Npossessing it is a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.28,0:12:50.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just possessing it is a crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.43,0:12:52.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to the people \Nwho could always use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.30,0:12:55.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.31,0:12:57.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You just make sure not \Nto have it on you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.83,0:13:01.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And wait, what do you mean people \Nwho could always use magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.17,0:13:08.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like in this \Nworld, magic is an object.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.57,0:13:09.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Object?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.54,0:13:11.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,By saying that magic is limited here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.58,0:13:15.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,it means that there aren't people like us \Nwho hold magic within their own bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.22,0:13:19.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Physical objects like lacrima \Ncan hold magic power.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.20,0:13:24.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So if you combine them with weapons or \Nother daily items, you create magic items.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.17,0:13:27.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's referred to generally as "magic".
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.36,0:13:31.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So the wizards over here \Njust use magic items?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.24,0:13:32.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.82,0:13:34.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.36,0:13:37.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a magic black \Nmarket underground here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.05,0:13:39.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll need it if you want to travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.39,0:13:41.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Black market?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.64,0:13:45.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess we gotta play by the \Nrules here to use magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.97,0:13:46.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.68,0:13:48.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You adapt quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.86,0:13:57.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At the same time, another Earthland \Nwizard can be seen entering Louen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.56,0:14:01.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, where should I start?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.90,0:14:04.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I should get it over with and ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.44,0:14:12.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. I'd like to ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.54,0:14:15.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.40,0:14:25.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This Edolas place don't got \Na lot of friendly people, do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.20,0:14:36.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like there's always some kiddies \Nrarin' to play with me though, no matter where I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.55,0:14:40.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You got a problem with us, bud?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.75,0:14:42.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You damn fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.79,0:14:45.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn fly? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.69,0:14:48.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ain't nobody else here but you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.26,0:14:50.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If ya don't like "fly", how about "maggot"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.73,0:14:52.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.88,0:14:58.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.18,0:15:03.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.21,0:15:09.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A huge lacrima showed up recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.60,0:15:12.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.52,0:15:13.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Spit it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.52,0:15:14.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.70,0:15:16.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.38,0:15:18.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you get a second helping...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.54,0:15:22.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! We really don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.14,0:15:23.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right? Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.24,0:15:24.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.08,0:15:25.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.35,0:15:27.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.10,0:15:29.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Get lost, you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.47,0:15:34.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Gajeel, since when \Ndid you get so strong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.17,0:15:35.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.00,0:15:40.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, until just recently, \Nyou'd never get in a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.02,0:15:44.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be another me that's here in Edolas?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.00,0:15:47.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, what's the Gajeel here do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.90,0:15:48.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.16,0:15:51.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just happen to look like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.25,0:15:52.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're joking, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.32,0:15:53.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You look identical.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.16,0:15:55.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever, just answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.64,0:15:57.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What does Gajeel usually do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.97,0:16:01.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a freelance writer here in \NEdolas with a terrible reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.75,0:16:02.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Writer?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.89,0:16:06.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All he does is write articles in magazines \Nand newspapers criticizing the kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.15,0:16:09.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he's hated by \Nall the people in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.40,0:16:13.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why no one would talk with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.75,0:16:15.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A freelance writer, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.10,0:16:17.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I kinda want to meet this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.05,0:16:23.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a whole lot of \Niffy-looking things lined up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.73,0:16:26.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This shop stinks of mold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.06,0:16:31.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because we have some antique \Nitems with a long history!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.28,0:16:37.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Mold, damage, smell... It's all part \Nof their mystique, dear customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.69,0:16:39.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care about mystique.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.69,0:16:42.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All I care about is whether they're useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.01,0:16:45.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a bunch of imitations out there, \Nso be real careful when you buy anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.44,0:16:47.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, old dude, you got any fire magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.57,0:16:52.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I have just the thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.31,0:16:54.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.28,0:16:56.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Edolas magic, flaming sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.55,0:16:58.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You charge it here, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.58,0:17:00.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! Amazing, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.65,0:17:03.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That flame's pretty weak, but \Nit's better than nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.29,0:17:05.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, you have very good taste!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.51,0:17:07.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.21,0:17:08.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's good about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.37,0:17:10.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's small and cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.68,0:17:13.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, look here. Choosing like that \Nisn't going to do us any good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.20,0:17:16.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's called an Air Bullet Gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.60,0:17:20.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like a cute container on the \Noutside, but if you open it a little like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.22,0:17:25.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wind Magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.74,0:17:27.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How romantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.30,0:17:29.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam, you have very good taste!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.03,0:17:30.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we'll take these two.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.64,0:17:33.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.06,0:17:38.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Each of them is 20,000, but I'll give you a \Ndeal and let you have them for 18,000 each!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.65,0:17:40.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty expensive...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.11,0:17:42.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wares are getting scarce, \Nso they're quite valuable...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.79,0:17:45.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, aren't we forgetting \Nsomething important?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.60,0:17:46.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any money?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.19,0:17:49.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.05,0:17:51.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a laughing matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.41,0:17:54.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All I have in my pocket are some biscuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.30,0:17:55.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy, pay the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.95,0:18:00.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Being pressured like this... \NMaybe I kind of like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.67,0:18:01.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.20,0:18:03.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine then!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.30,0:18:05.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll treat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.06,0:18:08.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no! I can't take money \Nfrom you, Lucy-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.17,0:18:12.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You really saved me when those \Nhoodlums showed up that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.63,0:18:15.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Naw, that wasn't anything much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.81,0:18:19.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, consider them a present from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.17,0:18:21.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Great, we'll take them with our thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.31,0:18:24.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, old dude!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.24,0:18:29.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike our Lucy, Scary \NLucy is really dependable!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.00,0:18:31.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you not to call me scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.78,0:18:35.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got a lot of pull around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.02,0:18:36.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've really saved us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.26,0:18:38.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.43,0:18:42.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm kind of interested in hearing \Nabout the Lucy over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.99,0:18:51.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm writing a novel?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.50,0:18:55.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm from a rich family, and use key magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.36,0:18:59.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Both of you are equally noisy, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.70,0:19:00.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't call me noisy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.43,0:19:03.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We just bought this... But how do I use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.19,0:19:06.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You stupid... Don't show magic \Nin front of other people!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.18,0:19:10.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you that magic was banned \Naround the world right now, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.97,0:19:11.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.37,0:19:15.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But magic used to be part \Nof your daily lives, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.81,0:19:17.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.96,0:19:21.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The bastards from the kingdom have \Nstolen away a part of our culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.91,0:19:23.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.60,0:19:25.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So they can monopolize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.49,0:19:31.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then if we beat the people from the kingdom, \Nmagic might come back to the world, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.79,0:19:33.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand how crazy that sounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.83,0:19:35.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way to fight the Royal Army!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.45,0:19:38.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did you follow us?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.00,0:19:42.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I wanted to tell you \Nhow to get to the Royal City.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.57,0:19:45.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't planning to fight or anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.23,0:19:47.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then! Thanks a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.17,0:19:52.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.01,0:19:53.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Seal off the entrance to the city!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.73,0:19:54.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Royal Army!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.00,0:19:58.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wizards from Fairy Tail, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.03,0:19:59.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.54,0:20:00.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We've already been discovered?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.58,0:20:06.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.72,0:20:08.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's try this sucker out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.70,0:20:09.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.40,0:20:10.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.87,0:20:12.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.41,0:20:15.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Carla, how do I use this again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.05,0:20:15.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How should I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.00,0:20:20.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shields?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.04,0:20:22.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,One more!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.20,0:20:26.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic power is limited, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.50,0:20:29.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All magic has a certain number \Nof times it can be used!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.00,0:20:31.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just once?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.04,0:20:34.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep the output in mind, \Nyou can use it about 100 times!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.22,0:20:36.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Capture them!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.50,0:20:38.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.50,0:20:38.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.69,0:20:48.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What have you done, Wendy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.21,0:20:49.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.08,0:20:58.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Over there! Capture them at all costs!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.25,0:20:58.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.65,0:21:09.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We've managed to avoid them, but we won't \Nbe able to leave the city at this rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.52,0:21:11.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The magic here is hard to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.90,0:21:12.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.00,0:21:14.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What'll we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.23,0:21:15.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't there another entrance?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.40,0:21:17.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.08,0:21:19.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We found you, Fairy Tail!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.68,0:21:23.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.07,0:21:23.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.06,0:21:25.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.44,0:21:27.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Lucy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.79,0:21:30.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm Lucy, but what's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.65,0:21:31.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.75,0:21:32.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.84,0:21:34.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That hurts, sheesh!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.55,0:21:36.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is Lucy here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.44,0:21:37.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.23,0:21:39.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Man...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.15,0:21:39.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to save her!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.36,0:21:41.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.99,0:21:45.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gate of the Scorpion, I open thee!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.66,0:21:48.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy-san, we can't use magic in this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.14,0:21:50.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Scorpio!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.90,0:21:53.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We are!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.33,0:21:57.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sandbuster!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.37,0:22:02.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.17,0:22:02.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.35,0:22:04.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.11,0:22:08.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going on a date with Aquarius now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.35,0:22:08.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.82,0:22:10.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.95,0:22:12.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.26,0:22:14.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I missed you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.75,0:22:16.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody explain what's going on...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.14,0:22:16.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.33,0:22:20.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.96,0:23:59.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy, how much longer until \Nthe Edolas me shows up?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.35,0:24:01.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask me...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.62,0:24:03.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to \Ndo when he does, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.97,0:24:06.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We could have a contest to see \Nwhose flames are hotter...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.02,0:24:08.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Or to see who's stronger, etc...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.92,0:24:09.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's plenty of possibilities!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.88,0:24:12.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu, we didn't come here to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.51,0:24:13.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You know that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.51,0:24:16.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Fireball!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.89,0:24:20.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, I know! I don't \Nplan on losing, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.21,0:24:21.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll fight him totally seriously!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.76,0:24:24.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I meant. But whatever!
